author: Neal Jones, News Producer/Editor
title: It's "Cueto Time" in Canada
text:
KANSAS CITY, MO (KCTV) - When he's bad, he's very, very bad, but when he's at his best, he is certifiably great.
Royals fans have seen both sides of Johnny Cueto. They've witnessed his lowest moment of the year, a Sunday Night Baseball massacre in Baltimore, when he gave up four home runs and eight runs in 6.1 innings. But, they also saw him throttle the Astros in game-5 of the ALDS last week. Cueto held Houston to just 2 hits and two runs over eight innings. He set down the last 19 men he faced, the longest perfect playoff stretch since Don Larson's perfect game in the 1956 World Series.
Which Johnny Cueto will Royals fans see Monday night?
This postseason, the Royals are 2-0 in games Cueto's started. He carries a 3.86 ERA in two postseason appearances.
That will be the major storyline at the beginning of game-3.
